2011-09-23  Gabriele Bartolini  <gabriele.bartolini@2ndQuadrant.it>

	Add 'error' key (when status is FAILED)

	Uses the new Backup class constructor (passes the Server object reference)

	Adds catalog information
	Functions that help retrieving catalog information have been added, such as 'get_available_backups' which returns a dictionary of valid backup objects (backup ID is the key). Added functions that, given a backup ID, get the previous and next backup in the server catalog. Added the new constructor of the the Backup class.

	Changes the constructor by adding a reference to the server object and adds catalog information in the show command
	The backup_id parameter has been removed from the constructor (never used). A new mandatory parameter has been added and it is a reference to the server object (to which the backup belongs). This allows to perform queries in the server catalog like previous or next base backup. This is the first step in order to allow WAL file size calculations.

